title: On this day in history, Sept. 8, 1565, St. Augustine — oldest city in North America — is settled by Spain
description: St. Augustine, Florida, was settled on Sept. 8, 1565, making it the oldest city in North America. It preceded the famous Pilgrim settlement in Plymouth, Mass., by 55 years.

title: Ted Cruz: Today's Democratic Party is all about California environmentalist billionaires
description: Sen. Ted Cruz discusses how California Gov. Gavin Newsom's attempt to ban gas-powered vehicles will impact the people of the state on "Jesse Watters Primetime."

title: Herschel Walker considers rising poll numbers a sign he's 'breaking through' the pro-Warnock media
description: Georgia Senate hopeful Herschel Walker, a former NFL running back, is pacing even with or better than incumbent Sen. Raphael G. Warnock after weeks trailing.

title: CNN's SE Cupp says Dem candidate Fetterman given a ‘total pass’ from the press in Senate race against Oz
description: CNN's S.E. Cupp called out the media for not covering the Pennsylvania Senate race fairly with the press is favoring Democrat John Fetterman over the GOP's Dr. Memhet Oz.

title: Sean Hannity: California in crisis as state urges citizens to conserve power
description: Sean Hannity discusses California's dire power as the state looks to avoid rolling blackouts with strain on its power grid on Wednesday's "Hannity."

title: Sen. Ron Johnson on restoring integrity of federal agencies
description: Senator Ron Johnson of Wisconsin joined "Hannity" to urge whistleblowers to come forward with information about America's federal agencies.

title: Tucker Carlson: John Fetterman has a long list of documented failures
description: Fox News host Tucker Carlson rips Lt. Gov. John Fetterman's leadership and argues why he wouldn't be a good senator on Wednesday's "Tucker Carlson Tonight."

title: Chris Cuomo attacks Ted Cruz for ‘spreading discontent’ instead of ‘progress’ amid Europe's energy crisis
description: Former CNN anchor Chris Cuomo went after Texas Sen. Ted Cruz in a tweet attacking the politician for criticizing the European Union’s self-imposed energy crisis.

title: Mark Meadows: We went from energy dominance to energy beggars
description: Fox News host Sean Hannity spoke with former White House Chief of Staff Mark Meadows about California's green energy policies and how they are failing the state.

title: Megan Hilty’s pregnant sister, brother-in-law and nephew dead after Labor Day weekend plane crash near Seattle
description: The US Coast Guard released the names of the passengers and crew involved in the sea plane crash off Whidbey Island on Sunday in Puget Sound near Seattle.

title: Rory McIlroy says he doesn't have relationships with former Ryder Cup teammates who joined LIV
description: Rory McIlroy has not been afraid to voice his opinions on those who defected from the PGA to LIV Golf, even if that means ruining some friendships in the process.

title: Michael Cohen claims DOJ is 'tip-toeing' around Trump as if he were ‘the supreme leader’
description: Former Trump lawyer Michael Cohen attacked the Department of Justice for refusing to indict or incarcerate Trump after the FBI raid on his home in Florida.

title: US Open 2022: American Jessica Pegula taken down by No. 1 seed Iga Swiatek in quarterfinals
description: American Jessica Pegula couldn't make it to the semifinals in the U.S. Open, falling to No. 1-seeded Iga Swiatek of Poland in straight sets Wednesday night.

title: Leonardo DiCaprio's ex-girlfriend blasts 'ageist headlines and comments' after his split with Camila Morrone
description: Leonardo DiCaprio's ex-girlfriend Kristen Zang slammed media outlets and online critics over "ageist" headlines and comments following his breakup with Camila Morrone.

title: Anna Nicole Smith's daughter, Dannielynn, turns 16: 'Mom is looking down'
description: Dannielynn Birkhead, Anna Nicole Smith's daughter with Larry Birkhead, turned 16 on Wednesday. Larry took to Instagram to share a tribute to his daughter.

title: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez mocked for GQ magazine feature: ‘WAIT, WHAT?!'
description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio Cortez is facing heavy criticism after being featured on the cover of GQ Magazine. In the interview, Cortez talked about future presidential ambitions.

title: Rand Paul blasts Fauci after judge demands 'misinformation' emails: 'America should be appalled'
description: Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., sounds off on "Jesse Watters Primetime" following a Louisiana judge's order for Dr. Anthony Fauci and Karine Jean-Pierre to release emails.

title: It's time for Merrick Garland to publicly address leaks in Trump investigation: Pavlich
description: Katie Pavlich says it's time for Attorney General Merrick Garland to address the recent leaks coming from his department on Wednesday's “Special Report.”

title: Yankees' rookie gives Bombers walk-off victory from jaws of defeat
description: Oswaldo Cabrera was 0 for his previous 25 entering his at-bat in the 12th inning on Wednesday afternoon. Safe to say he was due, and he walked it off for the Yankees.

title: California wildfires spreading as state gets walloped by brutal heat wave
description: Wildfires have broken out in California in recent days, resulting in multiple deaths, as the state deals with one of the worst heat waves in its history.

title: Jen Psaki to bring ‘passion’ for ‘debunking’ to new MSNBC show, calls backlash to Biden speech ‘bizarre’
description: Former White House press secretary Jen Psaki reportedly gave hints about her upcoming MSNBC show, noting she has a passion for debunking and "calling out BS."

title: Defending Super Bowl champion Rams are underdogs against Bills
description: The Los Angeles Rams will raise their Super Bowl banner on Thursday Night Football, but they will play their Week 1 matchup against the Buffalo Bills as the underdog.

title: Memphis police seeking suspect in string of shootings recorded on Facebook
description: A 19-year-old teenager is being sought in connection with shootings in Memphis, Tennessee, on Wednesday, police said, as the city continues to experience violence.

title: Canadian man charged in big rig drug trafficking scheme worth millions
description: A Canadian is in custody for his alleged involvement in an international drug trafficking scheme that used big rig trucks to ship narcotics out of Southern California.

title: Sexton rips EU president for telling people they need to reduce their electricity usage to 'flatten the curve'
description: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton mocked the European Commission president after she warned Europe may need to take action to 'flatten the curve' to fight against the growing energy crisis.

title: Prince George, Princess Charlotte and Prince Louis start new school year in matching uniforms for orientation
description: Prince William and Kate Middleton accompanied their children: Prince George, Princess Charlotte and Prince Louis on their school's preview day for new students on Wednesday.

title: Bears' Justin Fields gearing up for first full season in NFL after disappointing 2021
description: Justin Fields, last year's No. 1 pick of the Chicago Bears out of Ohio State, hopes to rebound in his second NFL season. The Bears finished 6-11 last season.

title: Big 12 commissioner has eyes on 'going out west' to continue conference expansion
description: Big 12 commissioner Brett Yormark wants to continue his expansion of the conference after nabbing four more schools, including Cincinnati. He has his eyes set out west.
